      "full_name": "Khoroshka Aleg Uladzimiravich",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Aleg Khoroshka is a Belarussian judge who serves in a Gomel District Court. He was appointed by Aliaksandr Lukashenka. He issued politically-motivated rulings against the opponents of the Belarusian authorities, which include a journalist of the independent TV station Belsat, Katsiaryna Andreyeva who received a sentence of eight years and three months in a penal colony. He is therefore responsible for serious human rights violations and for seriously undermining the rule of law, as well as for the repression of civil society and democratic opposition in Belarus.",
  "birth_info": [
    {
      "date": "1977-05-22",
      "circa": false
    }
  ],
